                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d859">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50/2848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Heath</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-23T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 23, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1835. Department’s 1140, October 22, 10 p.m., Chilean Under Secretary says that
                    in view information and welcome assurances given by Acheson, Chilean Ambassador
                    to Washington is being instructed to sign the draft UNRRA agreement but at the
                    first meeting of the Council to introduce a motion requiring unanimity on
                    questions of fundamental policy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Heath</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
